               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-75-person898">
                  RICHARD 
                  CONSTANTINE
               <interp inst="t18191201-75-person898" type="surname" value="CONSTANTINE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-75-person898" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-75-person898" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a milkman, and live next door to Leffen. I was passing his door, and saw the prisoner and another opposite; I noticed them. About five minutes after I heard of the robbery, and told the prosecutor if he went across the City-road he would find them. I am sure the prisoner is one of them.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18191201-75-person899">
                  THOMAS 
                  BRADFORD
               <interp inst="t18191201-75-person899" type="surname" value="BRADFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-75-person899" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18191201-75-person899" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a headborough of St. Luke's. I was in Peerless-row, and saw the coat rumpled up under the prisoner's arm; I asked him where he got it? he said two boys dropped it and he picked it up - I found it was the prosecutor's.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I saw two lads running; one of them dropped it, and I picked it up, thinking a reward would be offered.</p>
